.TH CLIP_CLIENT 1 "March 2026" "1.0.0" "ws-audiod"
.SH NAME
clip_client \- extract audio clips from ws\-audiod ring buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clip_client
.I start_offset
.I end_offset
.RI [ format ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clip_client
connects to the ws\-audiod control socket and extracts audio clips from the
daemon's rolling ring buffer.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I start_offset
Start time in seconds. Can be negative for pre-event capture.
.TP
.I end_offset
End time in seconds, relative to now.
.TP
.I format
Output format: \fBwav\fR (default) or \fBflac\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Extract a 10-second WAV clip:
.B clip_client \-5 5
.TP
Extract a 30-second FLAC clip from the buffer:
.B clip_client \-30 0 flac
.SH AUTHOR
Ed Baker <ed@ebaker.me.uk>
